getMarkupForNumerals

public static java.lang.String getMarkupForNumerals(java.lang.String part)
Returns the potential reg.ex. markup for a part if it is a Roman numeral or Greek letter. For instance, returns "[Aa](lpha)?" if the part matches "A", "a", "Alpha", or "alpha".

getProteinNameVariations

public static java.util.LinkedList<java.lang.String> getProteinNameVariations(java.lang.String name)
Analyzes a protein name (compound name) and returns a list of potential name variations to actually appear in text.
  • 'Acyl-CoA dehydrogenase, short-chain specific, mitochondrial' => 'Acyl-CoA dehydrogenase', 'short-chain specific Acyl-CoA dehydrogenase', 'mitochondrial short-chain specific Acyl-CoA dehydrogenase'
  • 'Sarcoglycan, alpha (50kD dystrophin-associated glycoprotein; adhalin)' => 'Sarcoglycan alpha', '50kD dystrophin-associated glycoprotein', 'adhalin'
  • 'SMT3 (suppressor of mif two 3, yeast) homolog 2' => 'SMT3', 'suppressor of mif two 3'
  • 'snail 1 (drosophila homolog), zinc finger protein' => 'snail 1'
  • synculein, alpha (bla) =%gt; 'alpha-synuclein', 'synuclein alpha'
